article.headline: Murray St. 78, Anderson, Ind., 33
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. (AP) -- Shawn Witherspoon and Tyler Holloway had 12 points apiece and every Murray State player scored as the Racers beat NCAA Division III Anderson University of Indiana 78-33 Monday night. Tony Easley added 10 points for Murray (3-6), the only other player to finish in double figures. Tyler Stotler scored 10 to lead the Ravens (3-3), who trailed 40-21 at halftime. The Racers finished 32-of-58 from the field for 55.2 percent, compared with 11-of-45 shooting for Anderson, or 24.4 percent. Murray dominated on the boards, outrebounding Anderson 46-17. Anderson tied the scored at 2-2 on a jumper by Keith Dabney two minutes into the game, but Murray led the rest of the way. The Racers' largest lead was the final margin.
